oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Fluctuation effects in oxygen depleted YBA2CU3O7-DELTA
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: BHATIA, SN
DHARD, CP
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Due to superstructural ordering of oxygen vacancies at the Cu-O chain sites in YBa2Cu3O7-delta, OI and OII phases are formed corresponding to the T-c around 90 K and 60 K. The nature of fluctuations including the pair breaking effects, change in interlayer couplings and other parameters have been studied for these phases.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: International Conference on Materials and Mechanisms of Superconductivity - High Temperature Superconductors IV (M2S-HTSC IV),GRENOBLE, FRANCE,JUL 05-09, 1994
